gate: LOCKED
sprint: S02
title: Address Validation Performance — UPS XAV Bridge Optimization
priority: P1
dep: none
env: localhost:3000 (FE) + Cloud Run dev (delivery-api) · branch:dev
status: PLANNED — scope refocused 2026-05-29, awaiting scope-approved
composite: crop                 # migrated 2026-05-29 — see instances/crop/INVARIANTS.md
repos: [crop-parts-services, crop-front]   # cross-repo: backend root cause, FE surface

description: |
  Customer report: address validation step in checkout is slow.
  Browser trace: POST /checkout/shipping — 970ms total, 968ms TTFB.
  Code-path investigation 2026-05-29 confirmed: the bottleneck is the UPS XAV
  bridge in CROP-parts-services/services/delivery, NOT the frontend.
  Sprint goal: quantify the bottleneck split (OAuth vs XAV vs app),
  measure the cache-opportunity ceiling, and produce a remediation plan.
  Implementation is OUT OF SCOPE (planned as S03 after T4 approval).

invariants:
  - Investigation only — no application code edits inside S02 unless a task
    explicitly approves a header-only Server-Timing instrumentation change.
  - Address strings are PII — any caching proposal must treat normalized
    address as PII (no logs, hashed cache keys, controlled retention).
  - CROP-search-hono is OUT OF SCOPE — verified 2026-05-29, no address code.
  - No prior INVARIANTS.md from S01 to link (S01 produced none).

ground_truth:
  - paths.code → ../../../CROP-front  AND  ../../../CROP-parts-services
  - project.config.yml
  - Customer report: address validation is slow.
  - Browser trace 2026-05-29:
      endpoint: POST https://crop-dev.app/checkout/shipping (Server Action)
      total_ms: 970
      ttfb_ms: 968        # >99% server-side
      download_ms: 1
      transfer_bytes: 423
      body_bytes: 152
  - Code-path map (2026-05-29 discovery pass):
      fe_call_site: CROP-front/app/checkout/shipping/_components/shipping-form.tsx:564
        notes: onSubmit only, single trip per submit, inside startTransition.
      fe_server_action: CROP-front/app/actions/delivery.ts:236  (validateAddressAction)
        notes: pure pass-through, no cache, no retry, error mapping only.
      fe_client: CROP-front/lib/delivery-api/client.ts:214
        notes: POST {DELIVERY_API_DIRECT_URL}/ups/addresses/validate.
               35s client-side timeout. Direct URL (bypasses gateway).
      be_route: CROP-parts-services/services/delivery/src/routes/addresses.ts:78
        notes: Hono route -> upsProvider.validateAddressDetails(address).
      be_provider: CROP-parts-services/services/delivery/src/providers/ups/ups-address.ts:30
        notes: Builds XAV payload + POST ${baseUrl}/api/addressvalidation/v1/1.
               No result cache. fetchWithRetry: 10s timeout, 2 retries, 500ms backoff.
      be_oauth: CROP-parts-services/services/delivery/src/providers/ups/ups-oauth.ts:27
        notes: Instance-memory token cache only, 1-min pre-expiry refresh.
               Lost on Cloud Run cold start / instance churn.

hypothesis_ranked:
  - A. UPS XAV provider call dominates (~400-700ms typical).             # primary
  - B. OAuth token miss on cold instance adds ~300-500ms.                # secondary
  - C. No result cache — identical addresses re-validated on retry/edit. # high-leverage
  - D. Cloud Run cold start adds container init time.                    # baseline
  - E. Network hops (Vercel us-east -> Cloud Run -> UPS).                # fixed cost

remediation_levers_under_review:
  - L1: Cache UPS XAV result keyed by normalized-address hash (TTL 24h).
  - L2: Persist OAuth token across instances (Memorystore / shared cache).
  - L3: Cloud Run min-instances >= 1 for delivery service.
  - L4: FE continental ZIP/state pre-check before round-trip.

out_of_scope:
  - CROP-search-hono (not in path).
  - Frontend caching/dedupe (no value over server-side cache).
  - Parallelize validate + rates (already not sequential at FE).
  - Switching providers away from UPS XAV.

success_metrics:
  - T1: 968ms TTFB split into oauth_ms / xav_ms / app_ms with sample n>=10.
  - T2: Cache-hit ratio ceiling estimated from 24h stage validation traffic.
  - T3: Ranked remediation pack — at least L1+L2 fully scored (impact ms,
    effort, risk, PII handling, rollback).
  - T4: Implementation plan for the chosen lever, sized for S03.

requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, VERCEL]
estimated: 1-2 days

tracks:
  - id: T1
    title: Server-side timing breakdown of the 968ms TTFB
    repos: [crop-parts-services]
    tasks:
      - S02-T1-server-timing-breakdown.pd
    requires: [VERCEL]
    gate: LOCKED
    output: sprints/02/S02-T1-server-timing.md

  - id: T2
    title: Quantify the cache-opportunity ceiling
    repos: [crop-parts-services]
    tasks:
      - S02-T2-cache-opportunity-quant.pd
    requires: [VERCEL]
    gate: LOCKED
    dep: T1
    output: sprints/02/S02-T2-cache-opportunity.md

  - id: T3
    title: Remediation architecture pack — ranked levers
    repos: [crop-parts-services, crop-front]
    tasks:
      - S02-T3-remediation-architecture.pd
    requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, VERCEL]
    gate: LOCKED
    dep: T2
    output: sprints/02/S02-T3-remediation.md

  - id: T4
    title: Implementation plan for the user-selected lever
    repos: [crop-parts-services, crop-front]
    tasks:
      - S02-T4-implementation-plan.pd
    requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, VERCEL]
    gate: LOCKED
    dep: T3 + human pick
    output: sprints/02/S02-T4-implementation-plan.md

stop_after: T4
next_sprint_gate: "User approves T4 implementation plan → PLANNER opens S03."
